   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Web Analytics - Analyse des Campagnes Marketing\n\nObjectif : mesurer les performances par canal (Email, SEO, Paid Ads, Social Media), calculer les KPIs cles et identifier les leviers d'optimisation.\n\n**Dataset :** Marketing Campaign Performance (Kaggle)\n\n**KPIs analyses :** CTR, CVR, CPA, ROI, Taux de rebond"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport matplotlib.ticker as mtick\nimport seaborn as sns\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\nplt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')\nplt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 6)\nplt.rcParams['font.size'] = 11\n\nprint('Librairies chargees avec succes')"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 1. Chargement et exploration des donnees"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["df = pd.read_csv('data/marketing_campaign_performance.csv')\nprint(f'Shape : {df.shape}')\nprint(f'Colonnes : {list(df.columns)}')\ndf.head()"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["print('=== Informations generales ===')\nprint(df.info())\nprint()\nprint('=== Valeurs manquantes ===')\nprint(df.isnull().sum())\nprint()\nprint('=== Statistiques descriptives ===')\ndf.describe()"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 2. Calcul des KPIs Web Analytics\n\nOn calcule les indicateurs cles utilises en web analyse :"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["# CTR = Clicks / Impressions\nif 'Clicks' in df.columns and 'Impressions' in df.columns:\n    df['CTR'] = df['Clicks'] / df['Impressions']\n\n# CVR = Conversions / Clicks\nif 'Conversions' in df.columns and 'Clicks' in df.columns:\n    df['CVR'] = df['Conversions'] / df['Clicks']\n\n# CPA = Budget / Conversions\nif 'Spend' in df.columns and 'Conversions' in df.columns:\n    df['CPA'] = df['Spend'] / df['Conversions'].replace(0, np.nan)\n\n# ROI = (Revenue - Spend) / Spend\nif 'Revenue' in df.columns and 'Spend' in df.columns:\n    df['ROI'] = (df['Revenue'] - df['Spend']) / df['Spend']\n\nprint('KPIs calcules :')\nfor kpi in ['CTR', 'CVR', 'CPA', 'ROI']:\n    if kpi in df.columns:\n        print(f'  {kpi} moyen : {df[kpi].mean():.4f}')"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3. Performance par canal\n\nQuel canal genere le meilleur trafic qualifie ?"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["channel_col = [c for c in df.columns if 'channel' in c.lower() or 'Canal' in c or 'source' in c.lower()]\nif channel_col:\n    channel_col = channel_col[0]\n    kpis = [k for k in ['CTR', 'CVR', 'CPA', 'ROI'] if k in df.columns]\n    canal_perf = df.groupby(channel_col)[kpis].mean().round(4)\n    print('Performance moyenne par canal :')\n    print(canal_perf)\n    canal_perf"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["if channel_col and 'CVR' in df.columns:\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 6))\n    \n    # CVR par canal\n    cvr_by_canal = df.groupby(channel_col)['CVR'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\n    axes[0].bar(cvr_by_canal.index, cvr_by_canal.values * 100, color=['#2196F3','#4CAF50','#FF9800','#E91E63','#9C27B0'])\n    axes[0].set_title('Taux de Conversion (CVR) par Canal', fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n    axes[0].set_ylabel('CVR (%)')\n    axes[0].set_xlabel('Canal')\n    axes[0].yaxis.set_major_formatter(mtick.PercentFormatter())\n    for i, v in enumerate(cvr_by_canal.values):\n        axes[0].text(i, v*100 + 0.1, f'{v*100:.2f}%', ha='center', fontweight='bold')\n    \n    # CTR par canal\n    if 'CTR' in df.columns:\n        ctr_by_canal = df.groupby(channel_col)['CTR'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\n        axes[1].bar(ctr_by_canal.index, ctr_by_canal.values * 100, color=['#2196F3','#4CAF50','#FF9800','#E91E63','#9C27B0'])\n        axes[1].set_title('Taux de Clic (CTR) par Canal', fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n        axes[1].set_ylabel('CTR (%)')\n        axes[1].set_xlabel('Canal')\n        axes[1].yaxis.set_major_formatter(mtick.PercentFormatter())\n        for i, v in enumerate(ctr_by_canal.values):\n            axes[1].text(i, v*100 + 0.05, f'{v*100:.2f}%', ha='center', fontweight='bold')\n    \n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.savefig('kpis_par_canal.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n    plt.show()\n    print('Graphique sauvegarde : kpis_par_canal.png')"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
